Ex. No:  — Create Basic Visualizations (Line Plot, Bar Chart) using Matplotlib in Python

From the FDS lab concepts using Matplotlib

Aim

To create basic visualizations such as line plot and bar chart using Matplotlib in Python.

Theory

Data visualization helps to understand patterns and trends in data.
Matplotlib is a Python library used for creating graphs and charts.

Line Plot → Shows trends over data
Bar Chart → Compares values between categories

Software / Tools Required
•
Python 3.x
•
Anaconda Distribution
•
Jupyter Notebook / IDLE / Google Colab
•
NumPy and Pandas Libraries



Program
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Sample data
students = ['Ravi', 'Anu', 'Kumar', 'Divya']
marks = [85, 90, 78, 92]

# Line Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))

plt.plot(students,
         marks,
         marker='o')

plt.title("Line Plot")
plt.xlabel("Students")
plt.ylabel("Marks")

plt.show()

# Bar Chart
plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))

plt.bar(students,
        marks)

plt.title("Bar Chart")
plt.xlabel("Students")
plt.ylabel("Marks")

plt.show()



Procedure
Open Jupyter Notebook.
Import Matplotlib library.
Create sample dataset.
Store student names and marks.
Use plot() for line graph.
Add title and axis labels.
Display line plot using show().
Use bar() for bar chart.
Display bar chart.
Verify graphical output.


